<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.124/260b.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>As soon as Colonel Gorgas arrives you will cooperate with him in every
                            possible proper way. The Chargé d’Affaires of Ecuador here informs the
                            Department that his Government desires bids from American firms upon the
                            bases of sanitation to be reported by Colonel Gorgas. The Department
                            learns that a reputable American firm will at the proper time present a
                            comprehensive proposal.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>